    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-15T02:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-15T02:36:00-05:00" n="1136"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4636.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-15T01:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1912—1 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Revolutionary situation greatly aggravated. Frontier conditions causing greatest
                    anxiety account international dangers involved. <pb facs="0941" n="825"
                        xml:id="pg_825"/> There seems to be, however, less bitterness, and if our
                    nationals in States of Sonora and Chihuahua urgently require relief, it could be
                    given without arousing much agitation. But in southern Mexico conditions are
                    very distressing, great increase in number of marauding rebel bands, whose
                    attacks are accompanied by unspeakable barbarities, mutilations, burnings.
                    Evidence of increasing inability of Government to cope with the situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
